{"word":"ἀνάλημψις","slug":"ἀνάλημψις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀνάλημψις, εως, ἡ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀνά\">ἀνά</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:λῆμψις\">λῆμψις</a></el> ‘taking hold’ formed from the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fut.\">fut.</a> of <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:λαμβάνω\">λαμβάνω</a></el>, the compound <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fr.\">fr.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀναλαμβάνω\">ἀναλαμβάνω</a></el>] ‘the experience of being taken up and away’, <b><i>departure</i> <a href='B:490 9:51'>Lk 9:51</a>,</b> which can be understood in the double sense of <i>death</i> and <i>ascension.</i> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀναλημφθείς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀναλίσκω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}